  "description": {
    "en": "**A Canadian Classic**\n\nA stirred cocktail featuring Canadian rye whisky, Bénédictine, and Angostura bitters.\n\n*   Known for its smooth and slightly sweet profile.\n*   Often enjoyed as an after-dinner drink.",
    "zh": "**加拿大經典**\n\n一款以加拿大黑麥威士忌、廊酒和安哥斯圖娜苦精調製的攪拌式雞尾酒。\n\n*   以其柔順和微甜的口感而聞名。\n*   經常作為餐後飲品享用。"
  },
  "historical_reference": {
    "en": "**Origin**: Canada\n\n*   Created at the King Edward Hotel in Toronto.\n*   Date of origin is debated, but likely around the mid-20th century.\n*   Named after the city of Toronto.",
